  "text": "Stereoacuity is naturally limited with a conservative threshold of about 10 seconds of arc [CITATION_1] . Considering this threshold and referring to Equation 1, the maximum distance at which stereopsis may produce usable data would be circa 1.24 km. However, in IPEs the angular resolution of pixels on a screen acts as an artificial cutoff to the theoretical capabilities of human vision.",
